    <item>
      <title>You May Now Kick The Bride</title>
      <author> starlost223 </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1786653/you-may-now-kick-the-bride/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1786653-you-may-now-kick-the-bride/chapter/1786655/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">56cecb287e7d64e8f6c970f5c7d71d118baa34e0</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 11 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bri Wilkinson is an ostensibly cisgender bisexual guy who has a beautiful partner, Stephanie Miller. Their wedding date is fast approaching, and Bri knows that their big day will have to be the most special, magical, and memorable one of their lives, especially considering Bri has been having severe depression and anxiety leading up to the wedding. Little does he know, Stephanie plans to make it magical and memorable in more ways than one, and plans to help "him" discover who "he" truly is.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;(closeted trans woman experiences severe dysphoria over having to be in a masculine role at wedding, her life partner helps her figure out who she is and how she will live her new life using powerful magic)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1786653-you-may-now-kick-the-bride/chapter/1786655/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Rolling the Dice&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;3 March 2024, CE&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Brian Wilkinson was the happiest man in the world. He had just graduated from the University of Washington a few short months ago and was getting ready to marry his beautiful partner, Stephanie Miller. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;For around 3 years prior, Brian had run a Discord server for DnD players in the Seattle area to meet up in person at a local U-Dub café and bond over coffee, drinks, and Nat 20s. Naturally, this attracted a lot of queer people to these meetups, and many regulars became close friends and found family with Brian over the years. But Steph was one of the first people who Brian was genuinely able to connect with on every level. She had wowed Brian from the first dice roll with her radiant blue hair, effortlessly confident attitude, and always making everyone in the room feel cared for and included. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Brian had always thought of himself as bisexual, but being 75% into dudes. Steph, though? She was the first woman Brian could imagine himself spending the rest of his life with. Funnily enough, it wasn't Brian who first realized just how into Steph he was. It was his sister Autumn, who was one of the first queer and trans people Brian had ever met – aside from himself, of course. Autumn was a self-described "raging lesbian" with fiery bright red hair and an equally fiery attitude. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In fact, Autumn and Steph used to date during their undergraduate days, and it was during those same U-Dub DnD club meetings that Steph and Brian first met. Strangely, a few weeks after Brian first started attending the university DnD club meetings, Autumn and Steph broke up, with the “raging lesbian” telling her brother that Steph had "worked her magic" on her and that she saw "how you've been eyeing Steph up. She's all yours, and maybe she'll help you fix yourself like she did me." &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Brian was initially quite suspicious of Steph after hearing of this; as far as he knew, his sister had never been a self-conscious person or a person who needed fixing, for that matter. She had always seemed so confident and outgoing to Brian, even before her transition. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p align="left"&gt;But something about Steph drew him in, and whenever she laughed or smiled, all of his worries seemed to melt away like hot fudge on a summer's day. As Brian bonded with Steph more and more, he became increasingly convinced that she was just such a good person that she brought out the best in even the most outgoing people like Autumn. He looked back on this now with a dewy-eyed smile, as he arrived at the mall to pick out a tux for his wedding day. While checking out some of the suits – and some of the hot twinks in the store, of course – Brian got a weird text from Steph.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
