      <title>The Egg Prime Directive</title>
      <author> MothMother </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1766594/the-egg-prime-directive/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1766594-the-egg-prime-directive/chapter/1766608/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">b9927fa65d06fc138f237039f689cab729d1707c</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 Aug 2025 00:13:27 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kitty is convinced that every bearded nerd with long hair and a kilt shopping at her foam weapons booth is actually a closeted trans girl. Her friend and business partner, Megan, is...unconvinced. Poor Kyle is just looking for a nice replica weapon, not a whole new gender! Sometimes a sword is just a sword, but when the sword is the fabled Stormbringer of Kitty and Kyle's favorite magical girl anime it becomes an opportunity for the impulsive prop maker to prove her theory, and change all of their lives forever.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1766594-the-egg-prime-directive/chapter/1766608/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;01. Captain Kirk levels of audacity, wrapped in leather and Neko ears&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;h2 style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;~ ♥  Kitty  ♥ ~&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I'm telling you, half the dudes who come through our booth are probably eggs!" I said to Megan during a brief lull in the flow of traffic.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Bitch, please! You can't know that!" Megan rolled her eyes at me. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I'm serious! The long hair, the denial beards, the boy skirts...."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Kilts, Kitty. They're kilts."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"....the kilts that go spinny. The purses....." I raised an eyebrow daring her to correct that to &lt;i&gt;sporran&lt;/i&gt;. Megan just shook her head. "I think they're all just trans girls, waiting for someone to release them from the masculine prisons they're autopiloting through the world."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Someone like....you?" She said, and I nodded gleefully. "Look, Kitty, you know I love you. But just because you wore kilts, and had long hair...and a denial beard...before you transitioned, it doesn't make every nerdboy and larper an egg."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"It's not just me, tho! Have you seen pictures of Erin from her egg days? There's a reason why the concept of the denial beards has become a cliche in the trans community." I maintained, refusing to let the subject drop. Megan sighed the sigh of a long-suffering friend who knew that once I got something like this into my head it was virtually impossible for her or anyone else to dislodge it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Even if I accepted your preposterous theory, you can't go around cracking eggs! It's a huge violation of consent!" She said.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Oh don't give me that 'Egg Prime Directive ' bullshit! And don't try to make this about consent. Living in a cisnormative society means that girls like us are forced into the closet by everything around us, all the time, without ever being asked what we would prefer. Me asking a girl if she wants to put on makeup with me and boof a progie isn't violating her consent: it's giving her a full picture of her options!" Now I was really working up a nice frothy rant! The kind that really got me going!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Unless &lt;i&gt;he's&lt;/i&gt; just a shy boy, who's into D&amp;amp;D, and Anime, and boffer weapons!" Megan said, exasperated.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Yeah, that is like...half...of my polycule. Or it was before they came out," I countered. "Now most of us are living our nerdgirl dreams as the women we were too shy to even &lt;i&gt;talk&lt;/i&gt; to before estrogen."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I'm telling you, they aren't eggs. There's too many of them! Trans folks are just a tiny proportion of the the overall population. It's statistically unlikely that there are more than a handful of us at this con." Megan had a point, but it was one I was prepared to counter.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Bullshit, babe. There's all kinds of positive selection bias in play at a gaming con," I said, ticking off my reasons on my fingers. "First, there's an increased probability that if you're trans you're also neurospicy. And don't you &lt;i&gt;dare&lt;/i&gt; try to convince me that this crowd doesn't already skew neurodivergent!" I said, and when Megan didn't contradict me, I continued, "Second, we're at GenCon. It's literally a whole convention dedicated to people imagining themselves into other worlds, lives, and circumstances! Nobody gets into gaming without some interest in experiencing life from another point of view! And third, these are 'boys' who are specifically interested in swordfighting and fantasy weapons! If ever there was a case of 'methinks the lady doth protest too much' it's this hobby!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Megan threw up her hands in surrender, "Okay! So what if some of them are actually closeted, even to themselves? What are you going to do about it?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I rubbed my palms together with mock villainous glee, and said (in my best evil genius voice) "I'm going to crack them!" &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I noticed one of our presumptively "cis" customers eying the anime swords. He had flowing chestnut locks that fell well below his (her?) shoulders, and an indifferently groomed reddish denial beard.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Starting with her!"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
