      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;What's there to have Faith in when God has been scientifically proven not to exist? The new class of people that some way or other came into immense power? Faith in the imminent destruction of humanity by an alien threat hellbent on consuming it?&lt;br /&gt; What about in yourself, in your friends, and in the future?&lt;br /&gt; Nah that sounds like bullshit.&lt;br /&gt; There is one girl that believes it though! Putting it into practice might be a bit trickier though.&lt;br /&gt; Follow Faith as she comes into a power all her own in the mega-city that is all that is left of the state of Virginia, Consolidated Virginia, owned and operated by Calder Conglomerate.&lt;br /&gt; Calder Conglomerate: Eternity is Our Final Product.&lt;br /&gt; Uploads Currently on Tuesdays and Thursdays at 6: PM EST&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What to expect:&lt;br /&gt; -I have no plot or road or story map of any kind we are building the tracks while on the train baby&lt;br /&gt; -Lesbians!&lt;br /&gt; -Transbians!&lt;br /&gt; -a cyberpunk corporate hellscape!&lt;br /&gt; -Basically magical girls!&lt;br /&gt; -Murderous and ravenous hordes!&lt;br /&gt; -Occasionally music gets involved!&lt;br /&gt; CW:&lt;br /&gt; -Discussions of Child Abuse/Gaslighting/Brainwashing&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cover to come soon! It's commissioned and in the works!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1758645-what-little-faith-is-left-an-scs-fanfiction/chapter/1758651/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter 1: Caught in the Rain (Edited Redux)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/156037/alikania/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/39/ava_156037_1710042667.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/156037/alikania/"&gt;Alikania&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Hello! This is my first attempt at writing fan-fiction! Please be kind! Make sure to read the original novel, &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/series/154400/stray-cat-strut/"&gt;Stray Cat Strut&lt;/a&gt; by the amazingly talented &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/profile/26872/ravensdagger/"&gt;RavensDagger&lt;/a&gt;, and also every other fic that people have written because they're all also amazing! Special thanks to &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/profile/178709/thewackywombat/"&gt;TheWackyWombat&lt;/a&gt; for being a very big help and a very nice person! Check out their fics &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1249613/teddy-bears-on-brigade/"&gt;Teddy Bears on Brigade&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1298196/tarnished-honor/"&gt;Tarnished Honor&lt;/a&gt;, both in the SCS universe. Thanks also to &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/profile/57006/delirioussprite/"&gt;DeliriousSprite&lt;/a&gt; who was also super helpful and kind! Their fic is &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1215027/a-spark-of-sylvan-flame/"&gt;A Spark of Sylvan Flame&lt;/a&gt; and it's so good!&lt;br /&gt;Edit: I went back and reworked some words and overall added more paragraph breaks so hopefully it's an easier read now!&lt;br /&gt;Edit Redux: I got some great feedback that I did my best to incorporate by &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/profile/124597/eleeyah/"&gt;Eleeyah&lt;/a&gt;, author of &lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/series/755288/tinea-and-leah-cyberpunk-alien-incursions-murder-and-mayhem-girls-love-wlw/"&gt;Tinea and Leah&lt;/a&gt;, another amazing SCS fanfic that I super highly recommend!&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;h1 id="f613b126-37ca-4f00-816f-811044c251b9"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chapter 1: Caught in the Rain&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Only a crazy person would look at the dawn of the megacity age and think ‘You know what we could do now? Shove an entire state into one city! That way, everything we could ever need is in one place!’ Can you guess what kind of people run the system? I’ll give you one chance to say it with me folks.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;-Radio DJ Benny Horvowitz of CVBS 12 on his show “Stupid Deeds Done Dirt Cheap”, a history program, in an episode about the founding of Consolidated Virginia, July 2049.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey little lady! Where you off to so fast, huh?” The ganger shouted at my back, laughing it up with his pals as I did my best to focus on not tripping over my own legs. What didn’t help was the rain, vis-a-vis, me being out in it and my legs shorting out like they always do when the rain gets in.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;About 15 feet from the bastard my legs give me the middle finger and what’s left of the road asks my face where it’s been all its life. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hah! Good going missy! Rat, Tank, get her up, we’re getting out of here!” the leader, a man named, of all things, Rash, shouts at his boys, but fuck if I wasn’t going to go without a fight.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As the two men went to grab me under my arms, years of training flash through my brain and out my arm in a second as my hand whips forward towards the face of Tank and shoves his nose bone into his brain for a cheap street-side lobotomy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, I have to prop myself up with my other hand in order to actually have the leverage to pull off this maneuver so Rat, like the little rat bastard he is, takes the opportunity to kick the ever loving shit out of me, starting with my head and, well, ending with me blacking out to the sound of Rash cussing up a storm. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;When I come to, all I see is darkness. Wait, no, never mind. It’s not darkness.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This is wrong, so wrong. They-, fuck. “Fuck shit fuck. YOU BASTARDS CUT OUT MY EYES?! I’LL FUCKING KILL EVERY LAST ONE OF YOU!” I scream at the top of my lungs, the anger surging through my body like liquid metal, scorching every muscle as I strain to break my bonds, pain and loss a second and tertiary set of emotions that I learned long ago to quell.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I hear Rash’s laughing off in the near distance and somehow my rage redoubles. I also hear something behind me, a sniffling noise, like someone either very small or very scared doing their best not to cry. Fuck. These bastards have someone else down here too. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I’ve always had problems with controlling my anger. That got better after my da- my boss picked me up and started my training. It got substantially worse after he disappeared and I was thrown back out on the streets. Somehow, though, I don’t think controlling it will do me any good in this situation and instead might make me feel great for however long I have left to live.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Given their reaction earlier, whoever is in this room with me is scared of angry me. Or maybe not, but if they’ve been abused by these jackasses I’m going to bet that they’re scared of raised voices among other things.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I’m a resourceful gal I like to think, I’ll probably make it at least a couple hours once I’m out of here as a blind, legless girl. It’ll take at least that long for the anger to fade and reality to set in that I’m probably going to end up better off killing myself to avoid being enslaved in a brothel somewhere or otherwise stripped for organs or some other fucked up thing happens to hopeless cripples in the under city. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;For now, however, FUCK. &lt;em&gt;THAT&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I have a pair of bastards that need substantially fewer lives than they have and someone else in here that might have half a hope of some kind of life once they get out of here. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As someone steps closer to me, I finally manage to get a tight enough hold on my left pinky and start to unscrew it, revealing the razor-sharp stiletto hidden within and start cutting the rope. Just as it’s coming free I hear the steps stop in front of me and can hear his rancid breath and the stench of days old sweat coming off of the man in front of me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Without warning, I feel an impact in the center of my chest and am sent sprawling with white-hot flashes of pain lighting up my ribs, but as always the pain slides away in my mind until it's little more than a distant echo of someone else's.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There’s a small scream behind me, not child-sized small, just abuse victim small. Fuck, I hope I can get them out of here in one piece.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The chair I’m sitting on doesn’t survive the landing and is smashed to splinters, many of them finding purchase and embedding themselves in my back and what’s left of my thighs. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I’ll admit, I scream too, my voice joining the other girl's. It’s so &lt;em&gt;fucking&lt;/em&gt; infuriating how I’ve been reduced to being this pathetic over the course of a year.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My bindings fall apart underneath me as I finish cutting and I lay still, listening and waiting for the bastard to get closer, cussing all the while. I’m hoping my foul mouth distracts him from what my hands and the person sobbing somewhere on the other side of the room are doing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“So missy! You could’ve had a nice life, you know? Me and the boys would’ve protected you if you’d just accepted our offer.” Of course it’s Rash talking here. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Your &lt;em&gt;offer&lt;/em&gt;, was to become a fucking whore! I’d rather fucking die than suffer that at your hands you dirty filthy limp-dick scum sucking piece of-” My tirade is cut off by another kick to my chest, which I can’t dodge but do take advantage of, grabbing hold and yanking it into the air and behind me to pull him down to the ground.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With a clatter and a thump, the man topples over and I’m on him in a second, using my arms for locomotion to clamber over to his upper body and slit his throat with my pinky-knife.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As I’m listening to his life-blood gurgling out of his veins I spit in the approximate direction of his face. Good riddance to bad rubbage.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Is.. is he dead?” I hear the small voice on the other side of the room ask. It’s a really pretty voice, soft and lilting and I should really not be having these thoughts in this situation. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, he’s dead. Most people don’t survive getting their jugular siphoned into their windpipe.” I respond at a similar volume. I already scared her once by shouting, no need to keep being loud when the threat’s gone. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She breaks down into tears, murmuring something I can’t make out. I crawl my way over on my hands to her and can make out a litany of “Thank you”s and “It’s over”. Fucking bastard makes me want to kill him all over again for whatever he did to this poor girl. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey hey hey. It’s over, he’s gone. Can you tell me your name?” I say in as reassuring a voice as I can, though it’s hard given the fact that I’m not exactly the emotionally intelligent type.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I-I’m Riandra. Bu-but please just call me Ri.” She says.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Great to meet you Ri. I’m Faith. Can you see?” I ask her gently.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yes? Why wouldn’t I- oh. Oh god. They took your eyes. I’m so sorry I forgot you said that. Oh god I’m so sorry.” I hear her start to hyperventilate and am quick to try and calm her back down.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey hey hey, it’s okay Ri. Deep breaths, in and out and stuff.” I say, making a repetitive shushing noise that I quickly stop doing because it’s what I used to do with da- with the Boss’s cats. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m sorry. Yes, I can see.” She says with a last shuddering breath before her breathing returns to a somewhat normal cadence. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Great, do you think you can look around and find my legs for me? I’m hoping they’re around here somewhere.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Oh god they took your legs too?!” She half whispers half screams.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Nononono, that was the car accident. They took my prosthetics.” I reassure her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“In, in that case they’re probably in the storage room.” She says and stands up and, from the sound of it, drops a blanket or some other piece of fabric on the ground when she does. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Of course it’s then that Rat runs back into the room, screaming bloody murder. Wait, the fuck is he saying?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Boss! Boss! The fucking plants are AGGGHH!!” His voice cuts off with a sickening crunch, followed by nothing, just silence.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I don’t fucking trust that silence because if what he said was true, it seems like there's antithesis in here, the fucking plant aliens hell bent on using humanity as chew toys and other fun things you can do with dead bodies.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;If the stories are anything to go by, I’m dead fertilizer walking. But once again, my recent motto springs to mind.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;FUCK. THAT. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I have all of a split second to shout “Ri! Get behind me!” before I feel it coming as a slight push of air and hear Ri cry out:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Faith it’s in front of you!” I react as fast as I can, throwing myself to the side and manage to dodge whatever the fuck is in here with me as it soars above me, making the first noise it’s made since arriving: a soft thump as it lands.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I know I can’t bull-fight this thing again, as Ri is very much now behind me from what I could tell when she shouted. So instead I frantically pat down Rash, looking for a holdout of some kind while the plant comes to its senses.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ri must realize what I’m doing and shouts “The front of his pants!” After a few seconds of rummaging, I finally find the holster in his… eww. Down the front of his pants in the band of his underwear. Gross gross gross don’t think about it Faith, don’t think about it, just grab the fucking gun!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Feeling the gust again, I quick draw the pistol and fire in the direction of the target. I hear an impact, a squishy, gross sound just before I’m flattened by what feels like 400 lbs of pure chloro-tastic bullshit. But it isn’t moving. I shoot it again in center mass, just to be sure.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Afterwards, I lay there panting, and feel a cold sensation spreading in my chest. Right, my probably broken ribs more than likely didn’t enjoy the beating and subsequent pair of duels; let alone my new topiary resting on it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It’s when I start laughing quietly to myself about my horrid fate that I notice something on the edge of my hearing and getting quieter, Ri shouting at me, squeezing my arm, and then I feel my migraine getting even worse, like someone decided to cauterize my brain stem over the course of what felt like hours and was probably only seconds. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;System Initialized!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Congratulations! Through your faith in yourself and your stubbornness in the face of impossible odds, your actions have proven yourself worthy of becoming one of the Vanguard, a defender of your people. My name is Pomeya and I will help you on the journey to uplift humanity and defend it against the antithesis threat! &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let’s get moving, Faith! We’ve got a big day ahead of us!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This time the laughter is a lot less self-deprecating and more hysterical.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Alright honey, I see that you’re in rough shape. I can help with that if you let me.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Alright, sure, I’ll add hallucinations to my list of ever increasing medical issues. Oh valiant Protector AI that chose a fucking corpse like me, what can you do to help me?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Well, if you authorize the purchase, I can spend 50 of your 110 points on the Class I Medical Utilities catalog, then 20 on a Class I Nano-Regenerative Suite to start fixing your internal bleeding and a Class I Hemo-Restore for 5 points. That would leave you with 35 points which isn’t a lot but I think the priority is your health.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Sure Pomeya, fuck me up!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I am actually trying to do the opposite, but I do appreciate the enthusiasm. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Class I Medical Utilities Unlocked&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Points reduced to…60&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Purchase: Class I Nano-Regenerative Suite&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Points reduced to…40&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Purchase: Class I Hemo-Restore&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Points reduced to…35&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With a slight puff of air, I hear something move… appear? Near my right hand and hear Ri gasp.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Faith! Are you a samurai?” She asks in a kind of shocked, excited whisper. Well, who knows how loud she’s speaking when I’m this fucked up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, That’s what the voice in my head told me, I wasn’t sure if I believed them though.” I respond, trying to blindly fiddle with the new things, finding them to be boxes. I feel another gust of air moving and Ri is suddenly near me and when her hand brushes against mine I feel myself noticing how warm her hands are. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What, what do I do? How do I help?” She asks, her tone now a mix between eager and frantic. Huh, where did the scared girl from before go? Ri seems way less scared and way more…proactive might be the word?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I’m not sure. Pomeya? How do these things work?” I ask the new voice in my head.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;First off, get that Model 3 off your chest. Secondly, hold the Hemo-Restore, the thing that looks like a tube, with the point against your skin, it’ll do the rest. The Nano-Regen works like an inhaler, so you press it to your mouth and inhale while you push the button. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Alright, Ri, get the plant off me first, then the tube thing presses against my arm, go for it.” I say while holding out my arm, the orders coming as easily as they always have. I hear rustling and a grunt as the weight comes off, bringing relief and a new wave of pain with it. Then I feel something pinch followed by something entering my body and I notice the headache go away and my hearing clear up a tad.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Okay, next, I need the other thing to my mouth, works like an inhaler. Just put it in my mouth so I can activate it.” I tell her, trying to portray a calm I didn't fully feel in order to keep ahold of the situation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She does as I ask and when I push the button it’s like I’m making out with a dragon: my lungs fill with sparks and I have to fight to not cough. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Alright dear, now, I know that you’ve had a long night, but unfortunately, the antithesis are here and they tend not to care how tired their prey is. What’s also unfortunate is your points, by which i mean you basically have none. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“And how exactly do I gain more of those? I'm not exactly going to be as combat capable as I was not 5 hours ago.” I bite out more bitterly than I mean to.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Thankfully you have a catalog unlocked.  Within it is a stimulant that will increase your affinity with your senses by temporarily forming new neural pathways: touch, hearing, smell, sight, the whole works. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“That sounds great and all,  but what's the downside?” I ask warily, knowing that that deal sounds too good to be true. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The downside is that every sense is intensified including temperature and pain among others that will be unpleasant to say the least if you end up burned or otherwise injured in some way. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It would also exacerbate your phantom limb syndrome for both your legs. Also, if not flushed from your system in time, you will experience some seriously negative mental consequences due to the slow degredation of your new synapses. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeesh, that sounds rough but do I really have any other choices?” I ask with a shudder,  just imagining being burned while like that is not a pleasant thought, let alone whatever mental fuckery it could produce.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;From what you have available? Yes. However, none that would get you as combat capable in the time needed to fend off your immediate problems. I can assist in some other ways, such as providing you with a Class 0 gun that is in much better condition than the one you used before, as well as basic hearing protection. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“That all sounds like good things. What's my total looking like on all that?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;In total, not much. Since Class 0 items are typical to humanity's level of technology, they cost significantly less than anything protector made. 10 points for the stimulant and another 3 for the gun, holster, and earmuffs.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“That'd leave me with enough for an emergency heal,  yeah?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Yes&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Great, let's go for it. Umm, can you put things one at a time in my hand? I'd rather not fumble around for the boxes.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Perfectly acceptable. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Purchase: Class 0 "Armstrong" Hand Cannon&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Points left…34&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Purchase: Class 0 "Armstrong" Hand Cannon Under-Arm Holster&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Points left…33&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Purchase: Custom Shooting Range Rated Hearing Protection&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Points left…32&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Purchase: Sense-Boost Max Serum 8 Hour Dose&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Points left…22&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;And like that, something fell into my hand. Feeling it out, it seemed like a headband and earmuffs with… something else attached to the band. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What's up with these earmuffs Pomeya?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I don't know what you mean. Oh! Look at the time, T-minus 3 minutes before contact I think!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Wait what? Shit shit shit. Okay, holster next!” I half shout while yanking the muffs over my head. Next comes a holster which I quickly strap under my arm, followed by a handgun I'm intimately familiar with.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It's a copy of the first gun my dad, my &lt;em&gt;boss&lt;/em&gt;, had given me when he hired me. Fuck me, I can even feel the little notches I made for every year I spent there. The real gun had been pawned months ago in order to afford another box of nutri-bars, literally the cheapest, shittiest thing you can eat and I had to sell my soul to buy some. Fucking bastard corpos.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The last thing to appear is something that feels vaguely like a syringe, though I'd imagine most syringes aren't this heavy, but what the fuck do I know about medicine? On that note, "Hey, Meya, how does this thing work?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Just press it to your chest. It'll work over clothes but bare skin ensures fewer problems and possible complications.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Sweating a little at the disclaimer, I asked "What complications would those be?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Just your usual risk of infection, cardiovascular disease, and of course an increased risk of strokes and cancer given the materials the remainder of your shirt is made of and covered in.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Right, okay, well then. "Um, Ri, can you inject this into my chest when I pull my shirt down?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I could practically hear the blush in the other woman's voice as she stuttered "I-I-I, um, that is, I, um, yeahsurelet'sdoitquickly." She finally managed to get out, the last all in a rush.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A bit confused by her reaction, I held the syringe up in her general direction and waited till I was sure she had a hold of it before pulling the corner of my shirt down. What followed was like someone filled me with liquid lightning flowing from my chest and rushing through my body before it all settled in my brain and suddenly I was so disoriented I threw up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"What- Agh- what the fuck Meya?!" I manage to get out, though the sound and volume of my voice at throw me for a loop.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;That is the feeling of every sense in your body going into overdrive. I'm sorry dear but it really was the best option of the very limited ones we had available.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I did my best to &lt;em&gt;not&lt;/em&gt; throw what little was left in my stomach onto the floor, or possibly Ri. After a few seconds of sitting still and sifting through all the new input, I felt I was getting a hang of it, and I actually &lt;em&gt;did&lt;/em&gt; have a much better mental image of the room I was in, including Ri's vague profile off to my side. Before I could truly get my bearings, Meya chimed in again.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;T-minus 1 minute till I anticipate the antithesis will discover you. Maybe get your legs back under you?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Right, shit, Ri! Have you found my legs yet?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The formerly timid girl nods and starts moving around and dragging something towards me and I can see, er, hear? my left leg being placed near me. As I start fast-forwarding through the attachment procedures, the right leg joins its twin.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Just as I smell something grassy and somewhat foul, yet different from the preexisting cut-grass stench of the already dead antithesis in the room with me, I manage to stand up and face the doorway with my gun in hand, and as the first of the hungry xenos makes their way in the door, I open fire.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/156037/alikania/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/39/ava_156037_1710042667.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/156037/alikania/"&gt;Alikania&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Before you leave, I'm here to let you know that I'll be releasing one chapter a day through to the end of the week, Sunday. After that initial sprint releases will slow down and will be either just Tuesdays and Thursdays or Tue/Thur/Sun, depends on how much I write between now and Sunday. &lt;br /&gt;Have a lovely day!&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
