      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Morgan realizes something about themselves and Alex is more than happy to help. Then maybe some other things start to make sense as well.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This is the first and only fanfic I have ever written so please don't be too harsh. And yes, this is set way before they actually get together.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1749156-s-and-dd-tier/chapter/1749164/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;S and DD Tier&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Morgan finally found herself walking out of her bedroom, even though her shoes felt like they were filled with lead. She knew Alex would understand, and that they would be fine with it, but it still scared her just a little. When you have a revelation like this, it really shakes your world. Not just the present, but also the past where you can look back and see all the signs that were missed. Still, she knew she had nothing to fear from telling Alex. After all they were genderfluid and that combined with their god-like powers allowed them to look however they wanted at any time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Finally looking up from her feet, she found Alex relaxing on the couch and watching a crappy sitcom about two roommates that were oblivious to having feelings for one another. Today Alex was in an androgynous appearance, so Morgan took that as it being a ‘they’ day today. That might change later, as it normally did, but it was no trouble. Morgan liked seeing them be able to take on any form that made them happy. Now, it was time for Morgan to ask Alex to do the same for her.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hey,” Morgan started. “Can I ask you something?”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Uh