    <item>
      <title>A Wish Come True</title>
      <author> Meteorologist </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1737563/a-wish-come-true/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1737563-a-wish-come-true/chapter/1737577/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">b525f9b76b1525fa4456391dfe33ed350ae883e2</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 21 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;For me, getting isekaied is a wish come true. A perfect body, magical language skills, and a new world full of people to meet is more than I could want, and all that’s left to do is to hope the Goddess giving me this chance is more ‘genie’ than ‘monkey paw’.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I’m sure that sly smile of hers doesn't mean anything… right?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A Wish Come True is a fluffy isekai romance about a carefree puppy girl.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1737563-a-wish-come-true/chapter/1737577/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;1/1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt;“Oh, and make sure I can understand the language too!” I called out just as the bright light began overtaking my vision, obscuring the abstractly fuzzy but otherwise pristine sitting room. The woman I’d been talking to nodded silently as her lips crept up the sides of her face, her sharp smile the last thing I saw before my new life began.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Then, like a television changing channels, the flash in my eyes faded into an endless expanse of blue.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ocean stretched out in front of me, rising up to the horizon where it met a sky a shade or two lighter. The waves were slight, not strong enough to summon white foam to break the nearly monochrome scene before me. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My other senses returned gradually as the numbness I’d felt near the woman faded into a buzz in my ears and then into wet sand between my toes, a cold breeze against my face, the slight sting of salt in the air, and the woosh of water ebbing and flowing from the dark beach. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I blinked, slowly at first, savouring everything I was feeling, and then quicker as moisture began to build up in my eyes. The chance for me to start over more myself than ever was overwhelming in the best way and certainly more than I’d ever hoped for.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My life, the one on Earth, had been…&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;What was it again?&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My mind struggled to put together a coherent memory while my gaze panned to the side, taking in the dock swarming with people and dotted with the tall masts of ships in the distance to my right, and the snow-capped mountains even further behind and to my left.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I knew that the landscape was unfamiliar, knew that my body felt different, but not what was new or what anything had been like before. Even swinging the minute hand back a few ticks in my mind was impossible; I couldn’t recall the details of the conversation I’d just had beyond the fact that it was important.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ultimately, there wasn’t much I could do about my memories except wait for them to come back or, if my gut feeling was correct, hope they didn’t.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;What I didn’t have a similar feeling about, however, was my body. Looking down, I saw small mounds on my chest, a white linen dress, and, poking out from below the mid-thigh hem, a shaggy brown tail.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My skin, which had been cooling quickly under the constant onslaught of the wind, warmed as my gaze remained pointed downwards, flicking back and forth between my chest, thighs, and tail.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, as much as I would’ve liked to figure out why looking at myself elicited such a strong reaction, the elements would undoubtedly win in a war of attrition. Given my lack of survival skills, reaching the docks I’d seen and its accompanying city was my top priority. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I just had to hope I’d find a road on the way.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;—&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When I’d started my journey on the beach, the sun had just started its descent from the top of the sky. Now, as I crossed the imaginary threshold between the city’s sprawling farms and its urban centre, the sun was partially obscured by the horizon, casting a long shadow next to me as I plodded along the road. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There was a good chance that I wouldn’t be able to find shelter, not without any money. Thankfully I’d drank from a stream on my way to the road, so I wasn’t going to die of thirst, but I was quite hungry. Despite the pair of fangs poking down in my mouth, I doubted my ability to catch whatever small creatures had been rustling in the bushes along the road. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Still, I couldn’t help but smile as my head turned side to side, taking in the city. Twisting cobblestone streets carved their way through stout wooden buildings placed almost haphazardly. A few stood out in the distance – a stone tower housing a large bell, the battlements of a distant castle – but most were one or two stories with dark, thick beams propping them up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;People were scattered about the streets with simple clothes not unlike my own adorning their body, though the whiteness of my dress probably would have stuck out were it not soiled from hours of forging through the woods.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Also, unlike me, everyone I saw wore shoes. Although the rounded stones of the street looked uncomfortable, it didn’t bother my bare feet at all, and neither had the floor of the forest separating the beach and the road. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The last notable thing – well the last &lt;i&gt;two&lt;/i&gt; notable things – was that nearly everyone that saw me stopped in their tracks and stared blankly at my ears and tail. No one had similar features to me, their ears being on the side of their head, and their tails being nonexistent or somehow hidden under their pants or dresses. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;With the first couple of people I’d seen, I thought they were the weird ones – I mean why &lt;i&gt;wouldn’t &lt;/i&gt;they have a tail — but then after dozens of people all looking the same, I started wondering if I was somehow the strange one. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My absent memories weren’t helping either. I vaguely remembered asking for my tail and ears to look like this, but how or why would I have done that if people like me didn’t exist? Did they live somewhere far away from here, or not at all in this world?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I paused in my aimless stroll, my tail drooping down and brushing the back of my knees as my gaze fell to the floor. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Was I completely alone? &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After a short moment of reflection and a shrug, I picked my head back up and continued walking with a wag in my tail and a hesitant smile on my face. There wasn’t anything I could do to change it at this point, and even if I couldn’t find anyone like me, the weirdly shaped people could still be my friends. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Speaking of making friends, I ought to ask someone for directions before everyone went to bed. Really, I should’ve done it with the first person I saw, but I was too distracted taking in the sights and looking for someone like me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I strode over to the side of the wide street I was on, waving at the tired looking man walking my way. “Ya-ho!” I sang, coming to a stop in front of him. At his confused stare I continued, trying not to bother him too much, “I’m new to the city, and I don’t have any money. Do you know of anywhere I can go to get shelter and food, or failing that, somewhere I can go to find work quickly?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The man continued staring at me for a moment before silently inching his way around me, continuing to face me until he made it to my other side, where he dashed away.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I tilted my head as I watched him, wondering if he was really shy or something. At worst I’d expected a brusque, ‘no,’ but I supposed there were people like that, too.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Oh well, there were still plenty of other people around to ask.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The next people I tried were a couple, a man and a woman strolling down the street with clasped hands. I asked the same questions in the same manner as I had before, but instead of responding to me, they began talking between each other as if I couldn’t hear them. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Before they spoke, I was starting to wonder if people spoke a different language here and that was why I was getting weird responses, but the couple spoke in perfectly normal English!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It’s kind of cute?” The woman started, a questioning inflection in her tone as she stared at my ears.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Cute?” He didn’t seem to agree.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yeah, it looks like a stray. Do you think it’s begging for food? Or pets…?” She finally pulled her gaze away from me to look at her boyfriend, who had a disgusted expression on his face. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It’s an abomination, the result of some twisted magic,” he spat, his lips twisting as he tried to pull her away from me. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Aww. Look, you made it sad!” The woman reached her hand up to the top of my head and ruffled my hair, squatting slightly so that her eyes were even with mine. “There there, he’s not usually that mean, he’s just jealous because you’re cuter than him.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Eww, don’t touch it!” The man pulled at her other hand again, this time succeeding in getting her away from me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As they left, I heard the woman laugh before saying something back at him that I couldn’t hear.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I hadn’t moved since I spoke other than to turn and watch them leave, staring blankly at the most baffling interaction I’d ever had. I couldn’t imagine that they were pretending about not being able to understand me, given that it would’ve been a thousand times easier to just brush me off than doing the comedy routine they had done. But if that was the case, I had no idea how they couldn’t have understood me; I was speaking the same language as them!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I growled and huffed before continuing my journey, determined to find someone who would help me. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The next three people I approached didn’t respond at all, two of them not stopping even as I called after them and the third a girl who was so scared stiff by me that I left her alone. Worse, the amount of people out on the street, as well as the amount of light, were quickly decreasing as the sun went lower and lower. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Then, just when I thought I was going to have to give up and sleep in an alley, I found someone different, someone who would surely be able to help me no matter what: a wizard.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Really, I couldn’t be sure if they were a wizard or not, but rather than the usual worn pants and dresses I’d seen from everyone else, they wore flowing robes with an embroidered collar. I couldn’t quite make out if it was blue or green with the low light, but the fact that it was dyed at all said that this person was different from everyone else, at least in economic status.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hey!” I called, approaching them from behind. They were on one of the narrower side streets, and I jogged over to them to catch up before they ran off like everyone else.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They stopped and turned around, revealing a long, angular face. They didn’t speak, simply watching me from high up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I hadn’t quite figured out my height, but I was about an inch or two below average compared to the people I’d seen, making this person, who was at least a foot taller than me, quite tall. “Hey, can you tell me somewhere I can find work, and maybe why everyone is so weirded out by me?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A few beats passed, and just when I thought they were going to turn away, they spoke, their quiet voice slipping under a breeze I hadn’t known was there.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Almost immediately, my fatigue overwhelmed me, my eyes drifting closed and my body swaying back and forth before pitching forward.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The last thing I felt was the unbelievable softness of their robes, and then everything went dark.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;—&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I awoke slowly, stretching my limbs out and yawning with my mouth as wide as it would go. My tail brushed against the cushion I was laying on and then curled up into the air, waving lazily back and forth. Apparently the wizard I’d met last night had gotten me to a bed, even if it was…&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Well, the first thing I noticed when I opened my eyes was that I was in a bedroom, but rather than sleeping on the four poster bed in the centre, I was curled up in a large dog bed in the corner. Next to me were two porcelain bowls, one containing clear water and the other two strips of dried meat. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I grabbed one of the strips and chewed on it while I looked around from my bed. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The room was large and extravagant, with matching curtains, bedding, and painted furniture all in a pale blue, complimenting the sandy colour of the wood floors. I couldn’t see any personal belongings on the nightstand, the dresser, or the desk, so it was probably a guest bedroom. I supposed that meant that the wizard &lt;i&gt;was&lt;/i&gt; rich. Either that or they’d fulfilled my request for a job and found me a position working for one of their rich friends.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Finished with the first meat stick, I slurped down some of the water and grabbed another, standing this time while my teeth tore through the tough, salty jerky. I was still wearing the same dress, although it was still a bit dirty, as was the rest of me. My body was also the same, and I could now inspect it properly with the mirror hanging on the wall beside the dresser. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My hair was chestnut and shaggy, much like my tail, and it fell down to my shoulderblades. My ears were the same colour, flopping on the top of my head and twitching with the sound of footsteps from another room, while my eyes were a darker brown. Otherwise, I supposed I had a cute, plush face, and a curvy silhouette; there wasn’t much to complain about.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I spun as the footsteps I’d heard got closer and the door opened, revealing the wizard and an older woman with hair half-grey and half-black. In the light of day I could see that the wizard’s robes, assuming they were the same ones, were aquamarine. The woman they were with was tall, although not quite as much as they were, and dressed in what appeared to be a military uniform, with blue fabric and golden trimming on her rufflely shirt and plain white pants with a sword strapped to her belt below. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They strode into the room with their eyes on me, but their attention on each other. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“&lt;i&gt;This&lt;/i&gt; is the gift you’ve been talking about all these months?” The woman scoffed, eyeing me skeptically as she halted a few paces away.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The wizard huffed a sigh. “I have completed the task you asked of me, your majesty, and I assure you that your daughter will be more than satisfied with the result. If you so choose, there is still more than enough time for you to procure another gift, but I request that you find a source other than myself, for I fear that if I failed to complete the task satisfactorily once, then I shall likely fail again.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The queen(?) pursed her lips, responding, “You know very well I can’t find anything with only three days left.” She took a step closer to me. “Is it even trained? Where have you been keeping it?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Um, guys, I’m right here?” I finally spoke, eyeing the two warily and waving to try to catch their attention.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I can assure you your daughter will be satisfied,” the wizard responded to the queen, ignoring me. “Now if you’ll excuse me, I have important matters concerning the safety of the kingdom to attend to.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Sit,” the queen commanded, staring at me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I stared back, wincing, and then glanced at the floor. “Here?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When she didn’t respond, I crouched down and sat on the floor, my knees curling to the side so that my shins were parallel in front of me. I figured listening to this rich lady was my job now, at least until she handed me off to her daughter. Things could certainly be worse, and likely &lt;i&gt;would&lt;/i&gt; be worse, if I tried to escape.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The floor was not very comfortable.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“See? It’s trained perfectly, your daughter will love it. Goodbye.” They didn’t wait to be dismissed this time, simply disappearing with a swish of their robes and a snap of their fingers.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The queen didn’t react, issuing more commands while I stared blankly at where they’d vanished from. I’d been calling them a wizard in my head mostly as a joke, but that was quite the magic trick…&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Lay down.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I glanced back at the queen before laying down on my stomach grumbling about how silly this was under my breath. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Roll over.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I rolled on the floor so that my stomach was facing up, meeting her haughty gaze with a bored one of my own.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Maybe it’ll be fine… She did want a pet when she was younger…” she muttered under her breath.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She turned and strode back to the door, stopping when she glanced back at me and saw that I was flicking my gaze from her to the empty bowl of food. Even if I couldn’t speak, I could still try to communicate.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hmm, you’re hungry are you? I’ll have someone bring you some food… maybe two portions, you are rather large…” She closed and locked the door behind her, not paying attention to if I’d heard her. I supposed she didn’t know I could understand her, even if  I’d followed along to her stupid commands. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Getting free food and a place to sleep was nice, but I wasn’t sure I liked the queen all that much. I hoped her daughter was nicer. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;—&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The next three days were dominated primarily by boredom. I got little bursts of excitement when the servants came three times a day to bring my meal, and again when they brought me to the baths, but other than that, I was locked in a plain room with nothing to do. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;At least the meals were okay, even if they were long-cold leftovers.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Knowing it was temporary helped me through it though, and I didn’t misbehave or even use the bed in the centre of the room out of concern that it could get worse. I had to believe that things would get better when I was given to the princess. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Something about the way the wizard had assured the queen that her daughter would like me kept my hope alive and well, even as I ran out of things around my room to inspect. At the very least I hoped that the princess was old enough to be able to take care of a pet.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Then, the three days were finally up and it was time to meet the princess and find out if I’d made the right call in staying – not that I’d had much of an opportunity to escape, with even the window locked tight.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I had breakfast as usual – the maid of course not understanding me when I asked when I would get to meet the princess – but later, instead of being given lunch, I was escorted out into the hall.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Much like when I was taken out for a bath, I was watched closely, one maid on either side of me as we twisted and turned through the halls. We were walking for a couple minutes with no end in sight to the various doors and offshoots, making me wonder how large the place was, but eventually the maids stopped outside a door no more noteworthy than any of the others, glancing at me to make sure I was staying still.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;We waited there with no conversation to pass the time or even a clock to measure it with. For the first few minutes, I tried to keep as still as the maids, but I quickly gave up and settled on fidgeting however I could, brushing my hand over my tail, rocking back and forth on my feet, and picking at my nails.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After what felt like several hours, but was probably twenty or thirty minutes, the door opened, startling me and revealing a third maid who grabbed my wrist and pulled me into the room.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Beyond the doorway was an extravagant dining hall, with vertigo-inducing ceilings and two tables that felt endless. Despite there being enough room for fifty or more people to eat, the only people sitting at the tables were the queen and what could only be her daughter, a shorter woman with black hair and a red dress. She was sitting facing away from me, so I couldn’t see her face. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I took in the sights as best as I could as the maid pulled me towards the pair, past the few maids ready to be called on near the walls and down to the end of the table with too much food for two people.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Once I crossed half the room I was able to hear the conversation, the princess saying, “You better not have gotten me another fiance for my birthday, surely even you can learn after the fifth time.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her mother sighed, “No, I didn’t this time, although there will of course be several eligible bachelors at dinner tonight, and I’d appreciate it if you at least &lt;i&gt;talked&lt;/i&gt; to them.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Sure, sure, of course,” she responded, clearly not intending to follow through, “So what’s the secret surprise then, if it’s not some poor sap?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The maid guiding me along stopped, the two of us a few metres behind the princess. She hadn’t heard either of our footsteps, the maid probably experienced at moving silently, while my bare feet didn’t make much sound on the plush rug running down the centre of the room.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The queen didn’t acknowledge us, keeping her gaze fixed on her daughter. “With some help from Alister and many months of work, I was able to procure you a one-of-a-kind pet,” she smiled, the wrinkles on her face curling as she finally looked up at me, causing her daughter to turn around.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As soon as her eyes met mine, I couldn’t move, couldn’t react at all, even when her expression went from shock to confusion and then wrinkled up in what could only be disgust. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The princess’ eyes were dark, with hardly any contrast between her pupil and her iris. The rest of her face was just as intimidating, her soft, smooth skin having no problems contorting itself into sharp, biting expressions as she inspected my paralyzed form.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She didn’t look like a vampire, not having pale skin or red eyes to start, but I got the impression that she would make a really good one, the kind that would steal your girlfriend only to dump her soon after when she ran out of blood.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In other words, I’d just found out I had a type.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What…?” she let out, still examining me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her mother stood, eager to sell me. “This is your new pet. She’s quite well trained,” she paced over toward me, regarding me with a stern stare not even half as sharp as her daughter’s, “&lt;i&gt;Sit&lt;/i&gt;,” she commanded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I hesitated, glancing at the princess, before doing as she told me. I wanted to make a good impression, especially if I was going to be stuck here, but I’d rather it was the princess giving me commands than her mother.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She ran me through the same routine of commands as when we first met, adding ‘shake’ this time, although she didn’t find it funny when I shook my head back and forth instead of shaking her hand. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The princess watched us intently, her confusion slowly fading into thoughtfulness. Perhaps she was thinking of potential uses for me, or she might’ve been thinking of ways to get rid of me; I couldn’t tell.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Silence descended after I performed the last command, the queen and I staring at the princess, waiting for her to react to her gift, while she stared right back, exerting pressure on us just by existing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I was the first to crack in our weird standoff, not having the stubborn pride that the two monarchs clearly did. Still on my hands and knees, I crawled over to where the princess was sitting, very grateful for the soft rug under me, and sat down just below her, staring up with what I could only imagine was something in between a pleading expression and a hopeful one. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As her gaze slowly drifted from me to her mother, her hand floated down to the top of my head, resting there for a moment before rubbing and scratching my scalp idly. My eyes fluttered shut as a wave of bliss washed over me. I didn’t really mind being held captive, unable to communicate, if it meant she would be the one looking after me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Above my head, back in the realm of humans, the princess spoke with an amused satisfaction, as if reveling in a victory no one else had noted yet. “Thank you, your majesty, for the wonderful gift. I’m honestly shocked you knew what I needed before I did, such is the wisdom of our great queen.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The queen hesitated before responding in a slightly nervous voice, “Of course. Alister helped a little bit, but it was mostly thanks to me.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There was a short pause before she continued, “Well, my queenly duties await, even on an esteemed holiday such as this. I will see you again for dinner, where you will surely find a fiance.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I have a good feeling about tonight as well. Good day, your majesty.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Once the two of us were alone, disregarding the several maids still around the edges of the room, waiting to clean up, her hand stopped its motions on my hair and she rose out of her chair, her crimson gown tightening around her fit figure as she moved.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When she strode off without a word, I followed behind, not having any better ideas. It felt a little awkward to stand up and follow her on two feet, but it was either that or lose her in the maze-like halls, and she was my favourite person I’d met so far in this world.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Once we made it through the halls, through her sitting room, and into her bedroom, I didn’t have a chance to examine my surroundings before she abruptly turned and fixed me with an intense stare.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What are you…?” she muttered, her dark eyes running up and down me in a way that made me shiver.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I shrugged, an action that caused her eyes to narrow and her lips to purse even harder.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“My name is Charlotte, and I’m your owner from now on,” she said with a flourish, curtsying and then going back to watching me intently when she finished.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Beyond noting her name in my mind, I was starting to wonder if I was supposed to be sitting. Charlotte was only an inch or so taller than I was, and so when she bowed even slightly, she was shorter than me, which made me feel odd. On the other hand, it would be weird for me to sit randomly on her hardwood floors without being told to, right?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I pulled myself out of my spiral before it could go far by focusing on the awkward silence. She was waiting for me to do something.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I gave her a thumbs up, indicating I appreciated her introduction. It wasn’t like I could give my own in return.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She seemed even more baffled by that, so I tried to help her out by explaining as best as I could, giving a thumbs up and a smile and a thumbs down and a frown until she got the idea.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Her eyes lit up in recognition before I made it through two cycles.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“You’re a lot smarter than they think, aren’t you?” I could see the ideas and plans whizzing behind her eyes as she took a step closer, regarding me with newfound fascination. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I gave a tentative thumbs up in response.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Can you speak? What’s my name?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Charlotte,” I responded quietly, sad at having to disappoint her. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Sure enough, she frowned, and her eyes unfocused and refocused as her thoughts accelerated. “Alister and my mother, did they do this to you?” she asked, gesturing at my ears and tail.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I shook my head and gave a thumbs down.  &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Hmm,” she let out, still dangerously close. Her eyes flickered down to my body and then right back on my own eyes, transfixing me. “I wanted to bring you to dinner tonight and show you off, what do you think?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I thought about it for a moment. The idea of trailing behind her while she did whatever it was she did at a fancy dinner party wasn’t the most exciting, especially when her mother was going to be around, but I did want to get to know Charlotte and seeing her interact with more people would help with that. There was also the fact that I was incredibly bored and twitchy after three days cooped up, so I would appreciate my new owner taking me out for a walk. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The princess gave me a devilish smile when I gave my thumbs up. Maybe I hadn’t quite understood what I’d just signed up for…&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Come on, we have a lot to prepare,” she said, grabbing my wrist and dragging me across the room to a door I hadn’t been through yet. Before going in, she gave me yet another once-over, remarking, “I’m sure I have a dress somewhere that will fit you… Although I’m sure you’ll look twice as delicious while wearing it – I’m counting on it.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;—&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Even knowing there were going to be a lot of people at Charlotte’s birthday dinner, I was still surprised and overwhelmed. I entered the ballroom clinging to her arm, a wave of recognition flowing out through the sharply-dressed guests and a cascade of inquisitive stares coming right back. Everyone wanted to catch a glimpse of the princess, and in doing so, saw me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I couldn’t fault them for that; she was absolutely ravishing in her navy gown that fell loosely down her body like a waterfall. Her face was obscured by heavy makeup, much like mine was, but even though we’d been attended to by the same maid, Charlotte managed to only look sharper under the blush on her cheeks and the softening of her face, like she was wearing a disguise to stalk her prey, whereas I looked silly and childish.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I tripped slightly on the hem of my own dress, thankful for the princess’ strong arm keeping me upright. My skirt brushed the floor as I walked, something I was decidedly not used to, nor was I used to the way the neckline dipped and stretched around generous cleavage propped up by a corset.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;At least my tail was somewhat comfortable for now, tucked down between my legs.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As the stares continued, I fought between hoping they weren’t staring at my ears, hoping they weren’t staring at my chest, and hoping they weren’t staring at my owner.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I knew on some level that we’d only just met, but there was only so much I could do to resist the unbelievably pretty woman who gave me pets and dressed me up like a princess – literally. It also didn’t hurt that she smelled quite nice – like honey and vanilla.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Back outside my mind, the humans were exchanging pleasantries, the first person already approaching Charlotte before she’d made it a fifth of the way across the room. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It was a man about the same age as us – although I only had a rough guess at how old the princess was – wearing an aquamarine suit and matching pants. He had green eyes, dark, rough stubble scattered across his face, and a rakish grin. “Greetings, your highness. I’ve left my gift with the servants, and although I’m sure you’ll appreciate it, nothing could compare to the priceless gift you’ve given me: your presence.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I flicked my gaze between the two of them as they silently stared at each other, Charlotte completely unamused and the man smiling, either oblivious or teasing her. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I quickly settled on glaring at him. While he wasn’t as bad as the queen, I already didn’t like him. I had a feeling I’d be doing a lot of glaring before the night was over.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Eventually Charlotte sighed and rolled her eyes at him, saying “It’s good to see you Henry… I suppose.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He laughed and shifted his gaze to me. “So who’s this, I don’t think I’ve…” He trailed off when his eyes met the top of my head, focusing in on my ears.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Go away, she’s mine,” I bit back at him, knowing that neither of them would understand me, and also knowing that it was the other way around in reality.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Charlotte smirked when he flinched back and her hand snaked behind me, wrapping around my waist possessively. “This,” she said, “Is my birthday gift from my mother this year.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Henry’s eyes narrowed and his voice lowered. “Are you serious? Does she know, or is she somehow oblivious to the implications?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“The queen is hardly one for knowing things,” she scoffed, “And there are no implications to me receiving a pet; it’s a perfectly normal gift for a young lady, especially for one without a bloke to warm the other side of the bed.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He was silent for a moment, before quickly grabbing a wine glass from a passing waiter and downing half of it. “Wow. And does it have a name? What even is it?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“For the latter, I’m not sure. The former…” she glanced at me, “I suppose I should name it, what do you—”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She stopped, interrupted by me squeezing her arm and glaring at her. “No,” I said, frowning.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Charlotte got the message, even if she couldn’t understand my speech. “I suppose it doesn’t want me to name it – name her?” she asked, looking at me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When I shrugged, she continued, “I suppose it already has a name?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I nodded and perked up, my tail batting against the back of my dress. I hoped no one could see it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Wait, it can understand us?” Henry boggled.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yes, she’s quite the smart little puppy isn’t she?” She turned to face me fully, pulling me toward her body with one hand and ruffling up my carefully styled hair with the other. “Yes, you’re such a good girl, aren’t you, you’re so smart.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I preened under her affection, already totally giving up on resisting her. She understood me so flawlessly and was sensitive to my wants even when she definitely didn’t need to be. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Char,” Henry hissed, trying to break us apart, “Have you forgotten where we are?!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The princess only pulled me closer, pressing our chests together. “There’s nothing strange about a lady showing affection for a cute puppy, don’t be ridiculous,” she said aloud, adding in a much quieter tone, “Besides, if everything goes according to plan, everyone will know how I feel about my present soon enough.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She pulled my head even closer, whispering into my ears for only me to hear. “Don’t think I missed how you look at me, little puppy. I saw where your eyes were while we were getting dressed.” Her voice had a mischievous lilt to it, and when she released me to a more respectable distance, she smirked at my flushed expression. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Henry interrupted again, “Are you insane? What will your mother–”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Dear, come with me to get some refreshments,” Charlotte told me before sweeping a disdainful gaze back to Henry, “Oh look, there’s some pretty ladies over there for you to bat your eyelashes at. It was nice to see you.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I watched Henry’s conflicted irritation as I was pulled away, giving up on understanding what was going on any better. I’d initially thought the people with weirdly shaped ears were like me when I first saw them, but after being around them for a short time, it was clear I was wrong.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Even my owner, who I liked quite a bit, was bursting with schemes, and while I would love to be the sounding board for her evil monologues, I had no interest in making my own similar plans.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Charlotte dragged me along through the party on a zig-zagging path to her mother. She grabbed a glass of something sweet, clear, and bubbly from a waiter, sharing a sip with me, and gave short greetings here and there to people she deemed important enough, but her focus never wavered from the queen towards the corner of the room, surrounded by a crowd of eager smiles.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;For a moment I wondered about the reason the princess had brought me, when her mother would likely take issue with a pet attending a party, but I quickly realised that I didn’t care and instead settled for sneaking glances at my owner’s pretty face and leaning into her every time we had to squeeze behind someone.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Even with her focus elsewhere, she couldn’t help but smile at my antics and tighten her grip on my waist. It was good to know she didn’t mind having a needy pet.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When we finally made it to the queen, Charlotte effortlessly parted the crowd with a simple clearing of her throat. Her mother’s eyes went wide upon seeing us, though she quickly settled into a more neutral smile. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Dearest daughter, I hope you’re enjoying the party… What exactly is that doing here?” Her expression tightened when she regarded me.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Greetings, your majesty. The party has been stupendous, and the guests much the same. As for my companion, I thought it only right to show it off, with how magnificent of a gift you’ve given me. To think after all these years of presenting me with marriage candidates since I’ve become an adult, you’ve finally found one that might stick.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; My eyes and the queen’s went wide at the same time. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Marriage?! She wasn’t supposed to marry me, she was supposed to feed me and take care of me and love me and…&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I blinked rapidly, trying to reboot my brain, and twisted my gaze to Charlotte who withstood the confused stares and hushed whispers alike. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“What a funny jest,” the queen proclaimed, not even bothering to laugh through her tight smile. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“It is no jest, and it is only with your great wisdom and magnanimity that I have even realized this part of me. She’s even capable of helping me produce heirs,” she said, beaming at me. “What a wonderful queen and mother you are.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I flinched, surprised by the fact that she’d seen my anatomy. I had been careless when we were dressing, not thinking that the princess had any interest in my body and too absorbed in my study of hers. For a moment I considered how I felt about her announcing it to the party, before again realising I didn't care about what any of these people thought, least of all the queen.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The idea that Charlotte wanted me, however...&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My tail began battering at the fabric holding it prisoner again.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Yes, of course…” The queen stammered, still stunned. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Guests’ eyes flicked back and forth between the pair, eager for more of the juicy gossip happening before their very eyes. A scant few seemed disgusted at the princess’ declaration – although whether it was because I was a woman or because I was a dog, I didn’t know –  but the majority either seemed to care little which way the discussion went or even seemed impressed at their ruler’s genius.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They should’ve been impressed with my princess instead, but it wasn’t my place to interfere.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I– you…” The queen failed to find a clean way out of the situation, instead settling for a compromise of a sort. “Surely it’s a concubine at most?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Now it is you that jests, your majesty,” Charlotte responded with a deep chuckle, “You have given me true love, and I dare do naught but grasp it firmly with both hands.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;At that, any ambiguity in the conversation was obliterated. She wasn’t joking, she wasn’t speaking in a roundabout way, she was straightforwardly discussing her deep romantic feelings for her pet.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Me&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Suffice it to say that dinner after that was awkward. When it finally came time for the majority of the guests to leave and the ‘important’ ones to filter into the dining hall for the main event, it seemed that everyone had heard about the queen’s gift and couldn’t help but take a peek.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Charlotte insisting that I be sat next to her – in a &lt;i&gt;chair&lt;/i&gt; – didn’t help matters, and neither did the fact that the chair propped me up just enough so that my cleavage was clearly visible above the table.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I wondered if that was part of her scheme – distracting people from my different ears and my inability to speak with my other assets – or if she’d just wanted to see me look good in a dress. At the end of the day, I didn’t care either way, although going from being treated like her pet to a rough equal gave me enough whiplash that I didn’t have the space to focus and decide if I even liked being her equal.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Maybe the old me, the one who had made the decision to be like this, had some kind of idea in her head about what being a dog-girl meant, but &lt;i&gt;I&lt;/i&gt; didn’t, and everything thus far, ignoring the boredom, had been more than adequate. I had been resolved to be treated like a pet – a loved pet, but a pet all the same – not a lover.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It was hard to imagine a world where I was both, not when the princess would eventually be a queen. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Charlotte didn’t have the same worries as me, or at least she didn’t show them. She smiled, dined, and sweet-talked her way through dinner with grace, even finding the time to feed me my portions whenever I looked too lost, surrounded by three sets of utensils and an artfully arranged pile of colour on my plate.  &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I endured though, pulled through by my willingness to let my ears flop shut atop my head and ignore the swarm of conversation around me. No one was expecting me to respond anyway.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When it finally finished and Charlotte pulled me out into the emptying maze of halls, I was overwhelmed and my tail was desperately itchy from being trapped in my long dress. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As soon as we were away from onlookers she stopped and turned to me, concern on her face. “I hope that was all okay, and I meant everything I said about you out there, even the part about me only discovering this part of me when I met you – even if that was meant to be misleading. See, while I’ve known lust for women as long as I’ve had lust, this is the first time I’ve felt whatever this is, and while part of my eagerness to jump on this opportunity is because I’ve been looking for a way out of marrying a man for years, I won’t deny that it is only because it’s you that I’ve summoned so much courage and–”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I had been nodding and shaking my head incoherently at her speech, unable to keep up with her quick words, but when it became clear she was going in circles and not about to stop, I silenced her by wrapping my arms around her and pulling myself in for a hug, burying my face between her collarbone and neck and inhaling deeply.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She relaxed and returned the embrace immediately, pressing her nose into my hair and squeezing me tight. We stayed completely still for a few long moments, only each other’s breaths and slow heartbeats disturbing the silence. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;My princess was the first to let go, sliding back and meeting my eyes with a delightfully warm expression. “Thank you… I– I’m so glad you’re here and I think finding you might be the greatest thing my mother’s ever done.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I rolled my eyes, partially because of how sappy that line was, partially because her mother had hardly done anything to bring us together, and partially because the line had &lt;i&gt;worked&lt;/i&gt; and showing exasperation was the best way I had to hide the crimson surely dusting my cheeks.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I pointed a stare at her and shook my head, poking her in the heart with one finger. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She understood immediately, as she always did, smiling wistfully and saying, “Agree to disagree.” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;We both exchanged sighs, tired from the long day, and her expression morphed into something mischievous. “We have something really important to do… now that we have some privacy.” Her eyes dipped down, taking my body in.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;That immediately reminded me of her earlier comment regarding my body, and I couldn’t help the slight hardness that formed under my dress. Surely she wouldn’t want us to make an heir &lt;i&gt;now&lt;/i&gt;, right?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Before I could think too hard on it, she grabbed my hand in hers, entwined our fingers, and pulled me through the halls, taking each twist and turn eagerly. If I’d had a chance to learn the palace’s layout better – or the focus to use such knowledge – I would’ve realised she was taking me nowhere near her bedroom, but in my mind, we were seconds away from rolling around naked on her bed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;So, when we finally burst through a set of doors and I found myself in the library, I couldn’t help but glare suspiciously at her. I had no problem with kneeling under a table and softly licking between her legs while she studied, but I had my doubts that was what she brought me here to do.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;True to my expectations, she led me to a table, let go of my hand, and dashed off, coming back soon after with a small book, a blank piece of parchment, a quill, and a pot of ink.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I gave her an unamused stare, glancing between her excited expression and where her dress was still clinging to her small chest.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She sat both of us down at the table, laughing, “Did you really think I was going to bed you before I got to know you? What kind of woman do you take me for?” &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;If I could’ve, I would’ve pointed out the fact that she’d already practically proposed, but instead, I settled for pouting at her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“This,” she said, holding up the book, “teaches the alphabet and– Wait, do you know how to read and write already?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I looked at the book with completely unrecognisable letters on its face and grabbed the quill and parchment, dipping the former awkwardly in the ink. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;‘No&lt;/i&gt;,’ I wrote in bold letters. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“I have no idea what that means,” she said, studying it with a confused expression.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I shrugged, not wanting to charades my way through explaining that I was fluent in a language that might not exist. It didn’t change the fact that I had no practical ability to read or write.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Okay, so I suppose you’re familiar with how letters work then, they each represent a different sound?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I nodded.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;“Whenever I find time, I’ll be teaching you to read and write, but I know you’re tired, so for tonight, we can do this the easy way and I’ll read the alphabet for you, and you can stop me when we get to the right letter. Really, I just want to know your name.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;I was still kind of peeved that we weren’t either naked or sleeping already, but when she looked at me with such tenderness, I couldn’t help but melt a little.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It only took a minute or two, and she had my name – at least my first name – written down on the paper.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She smiled at it, and then at me, and then at the paper, too giddy to use it immediately.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Despite all of my protesting and pouting, I had gotten swept up in her energy, and I could feel my sore tail thwapping against the inside of my dress yet again and the edges of my lips curling up into an involuntary smile.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Finally, after a few deep breaths, she spoke. “So… Nice to meet you Cocoa, I’m Charlotte. Want to get married?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;There was no way I could do anything other than throw myself into her arms, nodding excitedly – not in the face of &lt;i&gt;that&lt;/i&gt; smile.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
